# This git repository lives in the user's $HOME directory, which is full of
# environment data, caches, editor/IDE servers, and CREDENTIAL files
# (.claude/.credentials.json, .claude.json, .config/code-server/config.yaml, …).
#
# To guarantee none of that is ever committed, we ignore EVERYTHING by default
# and explicitly allow only the project's own files below.

# ── 1. Ignore everything at the repo root ───────────────────
/*

# ── 2. Allow the project files ──────────────────────────────
!.gitignore
!.dockerignore
!.env.example
!Dockerfile
!docker-compose.yml
!requirements.txt
!README.md
!*.py
!templates/

# ── 3. Defense in depth: never track these even if they appear
#       inside an allowed directory ─────────────────────────
.env
*.env
!.env.example
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*.db
*.db-wal
*.db-shm
*.sqlite
*.sqlite3
